## 3. Recycle Bin

Replace hard delete with soft-delete + recycle bin. Owner can restore with two options.

### State Machine

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    active --> recycled: Move to Bin
    recycled --> active: Restore (with access)
    recycled --> active: Restore (fresh, 0 access)
    recycled --> purged: Permanent Delete
    note right of recycled: All shares suspended\nFiles remain on disk\n30-day auto-purge
```

### Backend Changes

#### [MODIFY] [routes.py](file:///c:/Users/rogit/dev/Trustflow-local-dev/TrustFlow-Chain-of-Custody-based-Traceability-Framework/trustdocs/documents/routes.py)
- `DELETE /{doc_id}` → changes status to `"recycled"` (not `"deleted"`)
- All shares get status `"suspended"` (not `"revoked"`)
- File stays on disk
- New: `POST /{doc_id}/restore` with body `{"restore_access": true|false}`
  - `true`: reactivate all suspended shares
  - `false`: keep shares suspended (fresh start, 0 access)
- New: `DELETE /{doc_id}/purge` — permanent delete (removes file, revokes shares permanently)
- New: `GET /documents/recycled` — list recycled docs for owner

### Frontend Changes

#### [MODIFY] [Workspace.jsx](file:///c:/Users/rogit/dev/Trustflow-local-dev/TrustFlow-Chain-of-Custody-based-Traceability-Framework/trustdocs-ui/src/views/Workspace.jsx)
